\f3\fs26 \cf0 \
## What\
- Add SQLAlchemy SQLite dev DB + ORM models (Upload, Transcript, Segment, Summary, SummaryBullet, BulletCitation, UploadObject).\
- Initialize DB on startup; results survive restarts.\
- Implement background processing via FastAPI BackgroundTasks:\
  - status: queued \uc0\u8594  processing \u8594  done\
  - write stub transcript + summary with FK-enforced citations\
- Idempotent uploads by (meeting_id, sha256) across restarts.\
- Enforce caps: \uc0\u8804 1 GB file, \u8804 60 min duration (422/413).\
- MinIO scaffolding: helper + UploadObject table; optional blob upload when `MINIO_ENABLE=true`.\
- `.env` loading via python-dotenv; `.env` ignored.\
\
## API (unchanged)\
- POST /v1/uploads  \uc0\u8594  \{ upload_id, status:"queued" | existing status \}\
- GET  /v1/uploads/\{id\} \uc0\u8594  metadata + status\
- GET  /v1/uploads/\{id\}/result \uc0\u8594  transcript segments + summary bullets (with citations)\
\
## Dev receipts (ran locally)\
1) POST README.md \uc0\u8594  202 \{"status":"queued"\}\
2) Status after ~2s \uc0\u8594  \{"status":"done"\}\
3) Result \uc0\u8594  2 segments + 2 bullets w/ segment_id citations\
4) Restart server \uc0\u8594  status/result still available\
5) Duplicate POST (same meeting+file) \uc0\u8594  same upload_id\
\
## Notes\
- BackgroundTasks is a dev stand-in; plan to swap to RQ worker + Postgres + Alembic next.\
- MinIO is feature-flagged off by default (`MINIO_ENABLE=false`).\
